01:12:41.420 --> 01:12:43.580
But for a 70-year-old
device, I would

01:12:43.580 --> 01:12:47.050
say that's in
relatively good shape

01:12:47.050 --> 01:12:48.770
for going through the war.

01:12:48.770 --> 01:12:51.840
I can imagine this thing
got quite a bit of use

01:12:51.840 --> 01:12:52.851
during that time.

01:12:52.851 --> 01:12:53.350
Yes?

01:12:53.350 --> 01:12:54.266
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]?

01:12:57.390 --> 01:12:58.140
RALPH SIMPSON: OK.

01:12:58.140 --> 01:13:00.473
The question is, why did the
Navy switch to a better one

01:13:00.473 --> 01:13:03.770
and the Army and
Air Force didn't?

01:13:03.770 --> 01:13:06.100
I think it has to do--
and this is my theory.

01:13:06.100 --> 01:13:08.820
I think it has to do
with Admiral Donitz.

01:13:08.820 --> 01:13:11.590
He was skeptical
that this had not

01:13:11.590 --> 01:13:15.200
been broken, because
he was not-- I mean,

01:13:15.200 --> 01:13:19.820
he trusted his submarine
operators and commanders

01:13:19.820 --> 01:13:23.120
to be able to do what was
needed to fight the war.

01:13:23.120 --> 01:13:24.360
And they were losing.

01:13:24.360 --> 01:13:28.480
And there were enough
evidence that he

01:13:28.480 --> 01:13:31.450
thought that this
could be broken.

01:13:31.450 --> 01:13:34.520
On the other hand, it
could've been spies.

01:13:34.520 --> 01:13:37.320
You know, it could have been
other technologies, like radio

01:13:37.320 --> 01:13:39.610
direction finders or
something like that.

01:13:39.610 --> 01:13:41.820
But I think he was
suspicious all along.

01:13:41.820 --> 01:13:45.350
And so part of the
way along the way

01:13:45.350 --> 01:13:48.630
he came up and had them
design the four-rotor.

01:13:48.630 --> 01:13:50.390
The Army and Navy
decided they didn't

01:13:50.390 --> 01:13:52.890
want to go with that, because
it would have been quite a bit

01:13:52.890 --> 01:13:55.990
more work for them to them
swap out all these machines.

01:13:55.990 --> 01:13:58.960
And remember, there could've
been 30,000 of these.

01:13:58.960 --> 01:14:01.420
To swap those out in
that many locations

01:14:01.420 --> 01:14:04.500
versus a few submarines
and a few boats,

01:14:04.500 --> 01:14:08.120
it was easier for
the Navy to do that.

01:14:08.120 --> 01:14:10.400
I think it was a combination
of things like that.

01:14:10.400 --> 01:14:14.870
In fact, they interviewed
Admiral Donitz after the war

01:14:14.870 --> 01:14:17.910
and asked him if he thought
that the code was broken.

01:14:17.910 --> 01:14:19.440
And he said no way.

01:14:19.440 --> 01:14:23.080
And then in '74 when it was
announced that it was, just

01:14:23.080 --> 01:14:25.550
before his death, he
was quite surprised.

01:14:25.550 --> 01:14:29.560
So I think even though
he was suspicious,

01:14:29.560 --> 01:14:32.560
he still believed
that it was safe.

01:14:32.560 --> 01:14:33.940
Yes?

01:14:33.940 --> 01:14:38.132
AUDIENCE: So how
much more complex

01:14:38.132 --> 01:14:42.416
would it have to be for it
to be-- for them to have not

01:14:42.416 --> 01:14:45.490
been able to take 12 hours,
say 36 hours for them

01:14:45.490 --> 01:14:46.240
to break the code?

01:14:46.240 --> 01:14:46.701
RALPH SIMPSON: Yeah.

01:14:46.701 --> 01:14:48.159
AUDIENCE: How much
more complicated

01:14:48.159 --> 01:14:50.651
would they have had to make
it so that [INAUDIBLE]?

01:14:50.651 --> 01:14:51.401
RALPH SIMPSON: OK.

01:14:51.401 --> 01:14:53.120
So the question is,
how much more complex

01:14:53.120 --> 01:14:54.970
would the device
have to be that it

01:14:54.970 --> 01:14:57.850
couldn't be broken in 12 hours?

01:14:57.850 --> 01:15:01.950
And just adding-- not
even adding another rotor

01:15:01.950 --> 01:15:04.750
to the design, but adding a
couple more rotors to what

01:15:04.750 --> 01:15:09.404
can be selected from would
probably do that and more.

01:15:09.404 --> 01:15:10.820
That adds a lot
of complexity when

01:15:10.820 --> 01:15:13.390
you have these extra rotors.

01:15:13.390 --> 01:15:16.240
And if you only supplying
a few to some boats

01:15:16.240 --> 01:15:19.640
and some submarines, you
can probably do that.

01:15:19.640 --> 01:15:22.730
I don't think they
felt it was necessary.

01:15:22.730 --> 01:15:24.360
And so why didn't they do it?

01:15:24.360 --> 01:15:27.440
They had no suspicion that
this was broken, because

01:15:27.440 --> 01:15:30.890
of the care that was
taken to make sure

01:15:30.890 --> 01:15:34.520
that they didn't
misuse the information.

01:15:34.520 --> 01:15:36.450
The British didn't even
tell their commanders

01:15:36.450 --> 01:15:38.860
many times where
this was coming from.

01:15:38.860 --> 01:15:41.780
They would tell them this
came from a trusted spy.

01:15:41.780 --> 01:15:43.590
And so they would act
on the information,

01:15:43.590 --> 01:15:50.905
but not even know that it came
from breaking the Enigma code.

01:15:50.905 --> 01:15:52.340
Yes?

